As of today, this Pizza Hut location will not receive another penny of my money.  This used to be a great location but apparently, a change in management and/or ownership has made this place the epitome of unprofessional service.  My review is not based on one bad experience; it is based on a few bad experiences during different times of the day with the same issues.  Today's order was supposed to be delivered to me in 35 minutes, according to the email order confirmation that I received.  Once an hour passed, I called the restaurant to inquire about my order.  The rude employee replied "it's coming."  I asked the employee "when exactly?"  Then the employee replied "the delivery driver just left the store."  30 additional minutes passed and I called the store back to inquire; then a different employee said that the driver just left 10 minutes ago.  This was an indication that the first employee did not tell the truth.  Then an additional 30 minutes passed and I called back for the third time; I was on hold for several minutes.  Being on hold for several minutes with this location is also very common.  Then finally, after waiting on my order for close to two hours, it was finally delivered; of course, the food was cold upon delivery.  This place is full of workers with poor work ethic and a nonchalant attitude about serving the customer.
